## Spec-Driven Development

Always use Spec-Driven Development. Before any change, read in this order:

1. `.specify/memory/constitution.md`
2. `.specify/specs/<active-spec>/spec.md`
3. `.specify/specs/<active-spec>/plan.md`
4. `.specify/specs/<active-spec>/tasks.md`

## Rules

- `.specify/` is the source of truth.
- Only implement what is described in `spec.md`.
- Follow `plan.md` for architecture.
- Work task by task from `tasks.md`. Mark `[x]` only when truly done.
- After each change: explain what task was completed and which files changed.
- Conflict resolution: `constitution.md` > `spec.md` > `plan.md`.

## Commit style

Use conventional commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor:`, `test:`, `docs:`.
Reference the spec in the message when relevant: `feat: add user auth [spec 002]`.
